content:
"Historically, every time a Coinbase customer sent bitcoin, we broadcasted a single on-chain transaction. Starting today, we will be bundling multiple sends into a single transaction," said Eli Haims, product manager at Coinbase, in a <a href="https://blog.coinbase.com/coinbase-rolls-out-bitcoin-transaction-batching-5f6d09b8b045" data-v-f87c67ca="">blog post</a> on Thursday. <br data-v-f87c67ca="">
<br data-v-f87c67ca="">
"We anticipate that this will reduce our load on the Bitcoin network by more than 50%, and the network fees our customers pay will automatically be reduced by an equivalent amount when sending," Haims added.&nbsp;
